           <div class="news">
            <br/>
            <h6>
             News From the FBA
            </h6>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="http://www.fedbar.org/Education/Calendar-CLE-events/2018-Annual-Meeting-and-Convention_1.aspx">
                UPDATE! New 2018 Annual Meeting and Convention info now available.
               </a>
              </h4>
              Join the Federal Bar Association in September at the New York Marriott Downtown, situated in the heart of NYC's Financial District. Start planning your trip with the current housing information and latest agenda.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="http://www.fedbar.org/Leadership/Leadership-Resources/FBA-Awards-Program.aspx">
                EXTENDED: Deadline for the FBA Awards Program
               </a>
              </h4>
              The FBA honors individuals, chapters, and section and divisions with a number of annual awards recognizing exceptional service and outstanding achievement. The deadline for submissions is June 22.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="http://www.fedbar.org/Leadership/Leadership-Resources/Marketing-and-Communications/Midyear-Meeting-Resources.aspx">
                Midyear Meeting Content is Now Available
               </a>
              </h4>
              The 2018 Midyear Meeting "President Trump and The Federal Judiciary" podcast and other select materials now available.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="http://www.fedbar.org/Image-Library/Home-News/Issues-Brief.aspx">
                2018 FBA Public Policy Priorities
               </a>
              </h4>
              The association’s policy focus is on adequate courts funding, judicial vacancies, the need for additional federal judgeships, and the establishment of an Article I Immigration Court.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="http://www.fedbar.org/News-From-the-FBA/Bankruptcy-Judgeships-Legislation-Signed-Into-Law.aspx">
                Bankruptcy Judgeships Legislation Signed Into Law
               </a>
              </h4>
              President Trump on October 26 signed legislation (H.R. 2266) that extends 14 temporary bankruptcy judgeships for five years and creates four new bankruptcy judgeships.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="https://fedbarblog.wordpress.com/2017/10/06/faq-making-sense-of-the-jones-act-waiver-for-puerto-rico/">
                FAQ: Making Sense of the Jones Act Waiver for Puerto Rico
               </a>
              </h4>
              The Jones Act, as commonly known, is part of the Merchant Shipping Act of 1920, 41 Stat. 988 (1920). The act was sponsored by Senator Wesley R. Jones, from Washington State, which is how it acquired its name.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
             <li>
              <h4>
               <a href="http://www.fedbar.org/Outreach/SOLACE/Assistance-for-Puerto-Rico.aspx" target="&lt;blank&gt;">
                Relief Assistance for Puerto Rico
               </a>
              </h4>
              While the scope of the crisis in Puerto Rico following Hurricane Maria dominates the news across the country, the resilience of our FBA colleagues to recover and rebuild remains steadfast. Oreste Ramos, a national FBA leader and attorney in San Juan, has shared his firsthand account of conditions on the island and an appeal for continued support.
              <br/>
             </li>
            </ul>
            <br/>
           </div>
